== Bio ==

"I'm an independent journalist, citizen scientist, free culture advocate, and permaculture designer based in Aotearoa/ NZ. I've been involved in starting up and supporting the local versions of Indymedia and CreativeCommons, and coordinating the redevelopment of permaculture.org.nz. I've also been a test user of free code group decision-making on Loomio.org since it began accepting sign-ups, and I send them unsolicited usability and open source stewardship advice, from time to time (eg advising them to use GNU AGPLv3 as license). 

I've been attempting to map out the various packages and protocols in the federated social networking space in support of the [https://fediverse.party/ fediverse.party] guide website, an area I've been researching for a while as part of my [[Disintermedia]] project: https://web.archive.org/web/http://www.coactivate.org/projects/disintermedia/fyre-exyt/

I'm some way through writing a book about the experiences of taking of year long "net fast".

